<section class="card" id="whatsnew" style="border:1px solid var(--gold)">
<h2><span class="num" style="background:var(--gold);color:#1a1a1a">★</span>What's new in v1.11</h2>

<p>v1.11 is the <strong>"production readiness"</strong> pass — eight targeted fixes for going live, all flagged by
post-v1.10 review. No strategy logic changes; this is performance, safety, and signal-quality plumbing.</p>

<div class="grid-2" style="margin:14px 0">
  <div class="callout ok"><strong>1. Cached HIGH-impact news block</strong>
    <code>BlockNewEntriesDueToHighImpactNews</code> now reads a cached boolean populated by
    <code>CheckEconomicCalendar</code> once per minute. Pre-v1.11 this issued a fresh
    <code>CalendarValueHistory</code> call <em>per gate check</em> — up to 5× per ranker cycle on a
    live tick stream.
  </div>
  <div class="callout warn"><strong>2. DOM imbalance toggle</strong>
    New input <code>InpUseDomImbalance</code> (default <code>true</code>). Most retail brokers serve a
    synthetic B-book DOM that jitters wildly. If you see the DOM Context Bonus oscillating ±8 every
    tick on the panel, set this to <code>false</code>.
  </div>
  <div class="callout ok"><strong>3. R:R ceiling lifted for tight-SL setups</strong>
    <code>ClampProposalSlToRiskCap</code> now allows up to <strong>8R</strong> for SPIKE / NEWS_CONT / FADE
    (was hard-capped at 4R). Pattern setups (FLAG/ABCD/Level/etc) keep the 4R ceiling.
  </div>
  <div class="callout"><strong>4. Close-tag FIFO queue</strong>
    Replaced the single <code>g_LastCloseTag</code> string with an 8-slot FIFO queue
    (<code>PushCloseTag</code>/<code>PopCloseTag</code>). Partial-close races (TP partial + runner close
    in the same tick) now each get the correct exit tag in the journal.
  </div>
  <div class="callout"><strong>5. Throttled <code>ChartRedraw</code></strong>
    <code>UpdatePanel</code> now triggers <code>ChartRedraw(0)</code> only every
    <code>InpPanelRedrawEveryN</code> ticks (default 5). Trade fills/exits force-redraw immediately
    via <code>ForceChartRedraw()</code>.
  </div>
  <div class="callout ok"><strong>6. Adaptive retrace widening</strong>
    If today's <code>ARTR</code> exit count ≥ <code>InpAdaptiveRetraceTrigger</code> (default 3), the chop &amp;
    run retrace thresholds are multiplied by <code>InpAdaptiveRetraceMul</code> (default 1.20). Same-day
    feedback loop, so it self-corrects once the regime calms.
  </div>
  <div class="callout warn"><strong>7. Weekend-gap protection</strong>
    Friday after <code>InpFridayCloseHour</code> (default 20:00 server) marks
    <code>g_Session = WEEKEND_CLOSE</code> — no new entries. Existing positions still managed by
    AutoProtect. Toggle: <code>InpAvoidWeekendGap</code>.
  </div>
  <div class="callout"><strong>8. Tick buffer 200 → 500 + dynamic lookback</strong>
    Microstructure window now starts at 30 ticks but expands until it spans ≥ 1 second of data,
    capped at 250. Stable velocity/acceleration math during NY-open spikes where 200 ticks can fire
    in &lt; 2 seconds.
  </div>
</div>

