<section class="card">
<h2><span class="num">★</span>v1.10 reference (still in effect)</h2>

<p>v1.10 was the <strong>"actually trades and explains itself"</strong> release. Original v1.00 backtest blocked
100% of high-score trades with <code>risk $X &gt; cap $4.75</code>. This is the v1.10 changelog kept here
for traceability — every v1.10 fix is still active in v1.11.</p>

<div class="grid-2" style="margin:14px 0">
  <div class="callout ok"><strong>1. Hybrid risk-cap fix</strong>
    Each strategy first <code>ClampProposalSlToRiskCap</code> shrinks SL to fit cap (preserving R:R),
    then <code>ExecuteProposal</code> auto-shrinks lot when needed. Trades only get rejected if even
    the broker minimum lot exceeds the cap.
  </div>
  <div class="callout ok"><strong>2. Asymmetric position sizing</strong>
    Score 60-74 → <strong>50%</strong> lot, 75-84 → <strong>75%</strong>, 85+ → <strong>100%</strong>. Combined multiplicatively with regime mul.
    Inputs: <code>InpAsymSize</code>, <code>InpAsymMul_60_75</code>/<code>_75_85</code>/<code>_85_plus</code>.
  </div>
  <div class="callout"><strong>3. Per-setup-kind suspension</strong>
    Two consecutive losses on the same setup kind → that kind suspended for
    <code>InpSuspendDurationMin</code> (45 min default). Surfaced live on the panel.
  </div>
  <div class="callout"><strong>4. Spread-cost score penalty</strong>
    If spread eats &gt; 25% of T1 distance: <span class="chip red">-12</span>. 15-25%: <span class="chip amb">-7</span>. 8-15%: <span class="chip mute">-3</span>.
  </div>
  <div class="callout"><strong>5. DOM imbalance scoring</strong>
    Bid/ask depth |imb| ≥ 60% aligned: <span class="chip grn">+8</span>; against: <span class="chip red">-6</span>.
    Soft 40-60%: <span class="chip acc">±3/2</span>.
  </div>
  <div class="callout"><strong>6. Session-open window</strong>
    First 15 min after London/NY open: SPK/NEWS-Cont <span class="chip grn">+6</span>, FLG/ABCD <span class="chip red">-4</span>.
    Input: <code>InpSessionOpenWindowMin</code>.
  </div>
  <div class="callout warn"><strong>7. ABCD &amp; Level throttle</strong>
    Raw scores raised (ABCD <strong>62 → 74</strong>, Level <strong>60 → 72</strong>) and both now require
    <code>M5_ADX ≥ 22</code> (Level: OR confirmed magnet). Less noise.
  </div>
  <div class="callout"><strong>8. Setup category prior weights</strong>
    Final score multiplied by category weight: SPIKE/NEWS <span class="chip grn">×1.12</span>,
    FLAG/EMA/ORB <span class="chip amb">×0.95</span>, others <span class="chip mute">×1.00</span>.
  </div>
  <div class="callout ok"><strong>9. Exit-reason CSV column</strong>
    Every <code>EXIT_*</code> row now logs <code>exit_reason=&lt;TAG&gt;</code> — ANRD, ARTR, ABNK, AGVE, AEMR, ACUT, ATIM, MPRT, SL, TP, MAN, OTH.
    Also kept as a daily mini-tally on the panel.
  </div>
  <div class="callout"><strong>10. Brand-new diagnostic panel</strong>
    380×~840 dashboard with 6 sections, full per-top-3 block reasons (no more 22-char truncation),
    daily-P/L progress bar, suspended-setup list with countdown, exit-tally, DOM &amp; ATR fields.
  </div>
</div>

