<section class="card" id="overview">
<h2><span class="num">1</span>Overview &amp; Concept</h2>

<div class="grid-4" style="margin:14px 0">
  <div class="tile"><div class="v">11</div><div class="l">Strategy generators</div></div>
  <div class="tile"><div class="v">~3s</div><div class="l">Ranker cycle (HFT)</div></div>
  <div class="tile"><div class="v">M1</div><div class="l">Recommended TF</div></div>
  <div class="tile"><div class="v">0</div><div class="l">External calls</div></div>
</div>

<p>
  Each ranker cycle, every enabled strategy <strong>scans the market in parallel</strong> and proposes
  zero or one trade. Each proposal is a tiny struct with direction, entry price, strategy-specific
  stop-loss, three target levels, R:R, and a numeric <strong>score</strong>. The score equals the
  strategy's raw rating (e.g. Spike = 70) <em>plus</em> a universal context bonus (HTF confluence,
  ADX, microstructure, regime, VWAP side, spread, etc).
</p>

<p>
  The <strong>Ranker</strong> sorts proposals descending. The top one must clear
  <code>InpMinSetupScore</code> (default <strong>60</strong>) and a chain of hard gates (spread,
  daily-loss halt, news blackout, R:R floor, $-risk cap). Then <code>ExecuteProposal</code> opens
  the trade with the strategy's own SL price, capped by the global risk cap.
</p>

<p>
  Once in a position, <code>AutoProtectProfit</code> runs <strong>every tick</strong> with a layered
  defense — break-even, micro-lock ladder, profit-lock ladder, NORED (no red after green), retrace
  from peak, gave-back protection. Plus a 70 % high-water trail every <code>InpAPTrailIntervalSec</code>.
</p>

<div class="callout">
  <strong>Why this beats a single hardcoded strategy</strong>
  Markets cycle through trend / chop / spike / news / range. By running 11 specialized hunters in
  parallel and picking the best-scoring one, the EA naturally adapts to <em>whatever</em> the
  market is doing right now. Trending? <span class="chip grn">Flag</span>
  <span class="chip grn">EMA Pullback</span> dominate. Ranging at a level?
  <span class="chip ppl">Bounce</span> <span class="chip ppl">Fade</span>. Explosive?
  <span class="chip red">Spike</span> <span class="chip red">News-Cont</span>.
</div>
</section>

