<section class="card" id="faq">
<h2><span class="num">14</span>FAQ</h2>

<h3>Does it use any AI?</h3>
<p>No. It's pure deterministic algorithm. No OpenAI, no neural net, no remote calls. Same machine
every time.</p>

<h3>Will it work on a $50 account?</h3>
<p>Default <code>InpLotSize = 0.01</code> (micro-lot) and <code>InpMaxRiskDollars = 6.00</code>
fits a small account. But check your broker's minimum lot — if 0.01 produces $1+ swings on a
small account, drop <code>InpMaxDailyLoss</code> to keep yourself out of trouble.</p>

<h3>What broker / symbol do I need?</h3>
<p>Any MT5 broker offering Gold (XAUUSD). The strategies use $10 round-number levels and
ATR-relative thresholds, so they adapt to brokers that price gold at $1,800, $2,400, $3,000, etc.
without changes.</p>

<h3>Will it pyramid / open multiple trades?</h3>
<p>Not by default. <code>InpMaxPositions = 1</code>. The ranker won't open a second trade until
the first one closes.</p>

<h3>Do I need to set up <code>WebRequest</code>?</h3>
<p>No. There are zero outbound HTTP calls.</p>

<h3>Is it safe to run alongside the AI scalper?</h3>
<p>Yes. Different magic number (998877 vs 778899) and different CSV journal. Each EA only manages
its own positions.</p>

<h3>Why don't I see any trades?</h3>
<p>Check the panel's <strong>Verdict</strong> line:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>NO_PROPOSAL</strong> → market is too quiet for any setup. Wait, or lower thresholds.</li>
  <li><strong>BELOW_THRESH (45 &lt; 60)</strong> → setups are detecting but not strong enough. Lower <code>InpMinSetupScore</code>.</li>
  <li><strong>GATED FLAG (spread spike)</strong> → top setup blocked by a gate. Reason in parentheses.</li>
</ul>
<p>Also check Experts tab for skip messages if <code>InpVerboseSkips = true</code>.</p>

<h3>Can I disable individual strategies?</h3>
<p>Yes — every strategy has its own <code>InpEnableXXX</code> input. Toggle off any you don't
want, the ranker simply won't see proposals from it.</p>

<h3>How do I know which strategy opened a trade?</h3>
<p>Three places:</p>
<ol>
  <li>The on-chart panel POSITION box shows the setup name + score</li>
  <li>The MT5 order comment is prefixed with the strategy tag (e.g. <code>SPK-95-B:...</code>)</li>
  <li>The CSV journal's <code>secondary</code> column on every <code>EXIT_*</code> row contains <code>open_setup=&lt;name&gt;</code></li>
</ol>
